----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version 2.3 (25 June 2021)

[General Updates]

  * package updates to support RHEL8.4 variants. Note that changes in the distro provided hwloc required rebuilds of
    both OpenPBS and SLURM (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/1324)
  * addition of a Rocky 8.4 recipe. The `docs-ohpc` rpm includes a Rocky based recipe that mimics the CentOS
    Warewulf variant but uses an alternative "rocky-8" template when calling `wwmkchroot`

[Known Issues]

  * At present, a Lustre-client build is not available for a RHEL 8.4 kernel.  If Lustre client functionality is desired,
    users are encouraged to stick with a RHEL 8.3 kernel until a newer Lustre version is released upstream.

[Component Version Changes]

  * EasyBuild-ohpc                           (4.3.3 -> 4.3.4)
  * docs-ohpc                                (2.1.0 -> 2.3.0)
  * libfabric-ohpc                           (1.11.2 -> 1.12.1)
  * openpbs-client-ohpc                      (20.0.0 -> 20.0.1)
  * openpbs-devel-ohpc                       (20.0.0 -> 20.0.1)
  * openpbs-execution-ohpc                   (20.0.0 -> 20.0.1)
  * openpbs-server-ohpc                      (20.0.0 -> 20.0.1)
  * test-suite-ohpc                          (2.1.0 -> 2.3.0)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version 2.2 (01 June 2021)

[General Updates]

  * updated SLURM version to address CVE-2021-31215
  * updated CentOS installation docs to use newer name for the powertools repository
    (see https://wiki.centos.org/Manuals/ReleaseNotes/CentOS8.2011#Yum_repo_file_and_repoid_changes)
  * addition of Rocky 8 template for Warewulf provisioning. Although not officially supported, a template to create
    images using the Rocky 8.3 release candidate is included in the latest warewulf-vnfs package.  Users interested in
    provisioning a Rocky-based system can follow the existing OpenHPC CentOS recipes and use the "rocky-8" template
    instead of "centos-8" when calling `wwmkchroot` 

[Component Version Changes]

  * EasyBuild-ohpc                           (4.3.3 -> 4.3.4)
  * docs-ohpc                                (2.1.0 -> 2.2.0)
  * slurm-contribs-ohpc                      (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-devel-ohpc                         (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-example-configs-ohpc               (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-libpmi-ohpc                        (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-ohpc                               (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-openlava-ohpc                      (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-pam_slurm-ohpc                     (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-perlapi-ohpc                       (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-slurmctld-ohpc                     (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-slurmd-ohpc                        (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-slurmdbd-ohpc                      (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-sview-ohpc                         (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)
  * slurm-torque-ohpc                        (20.11.3 -> 20.11.7)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version 2.1 (06 April 2021)

[General Updates]

  * updates to support CentOS8.3
  * update packaging to allow co-install of multiple versions for development packages
    (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/1292)
  * documentation updates for starting tftp services (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/1286)
  * re-enable separate build of the sview package for SLURM (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/1289)
  * patch Warewulf for stateful provisioning (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/1291)
  * fix NHC binary paths for Leap (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/1295)
  * enable bash completion for singularity on load (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/1309)
  * variety of component version updates and other additions highlighted further below

[Important Highlights/Notices for v2.1]

  * the newer version of SLURM included in this release deprecates the accounting_storage/filetxt option. If you were
    using this configuration locally, you will need to comment out this plugin in slurm.conf or will encounter an error on
    startup. Sites previously dependent on this functionality for simple accounting mechanisms may want to consider
    replacing with the ascii job completion file option (JobCompType=jobcomp/filetxt).
  * the Arm Compiler for Linux v21.0 is incompatible with the OpenHPC 2.x series

[Component Additions]
  * magpie-ohpc                              (2.5)
  * slurm-sview-ohpc                         (20.11.3)

[Component Version Changes]
  * EasyBuild-ohpc                           (4.3.0 -> 4.3.3)
