----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version 2.0 RC1 (05 June 2020)

[2.x Series]

  * This initial release candidate (2.0 RC1) represents a significant update for OpenHPC to target support for two new
    major OS distro versions: CentOS8.1 and OpenSUSE Leap 15.1.

     o As the OpenHPC 2.x series targets major new distro versions, please note that the 2.x series 
       is **not** backwards compatible with the OpenHPC 1.3.x series.
     o OpenHPC 2.x is intended for fresh installs with the newer distro versions (or containers based 
       on these distro versions).

  * Note that 2.x builds for SUSE based systems are now performed against Leap instead of SLES.  Leap 15.1 is intended
    to be compatible with SLES 15 SP1.

  * Systems that start with 2.0RC1 installs will be able to upgrade to future 2.X releases.

[Important Highlights/Notices]

  * A new compiler variant (gnu9) is introduced with this release
  * A new openmpi variant (openmpi4) is introduced with this release
  * MPICH builds now use the newer ch4 interface
  * 2.x introduces the use of two related transport layers for MPICH and OpenMPI family builds that support a variety of
    underlying fabrics: UCX (Unified Communication X) and OFI (OpenFabrics interfaces)
  * 2.x also introduces initial 3rd party builds against the Arm Linux compiler for aarch64
  * 2.x package repositories are now hosted on a new site: http://repos.openhpc.community

[General]

  * nagios, munge, and clustershell installs in recipes now leverage distro-provided versions
  * ip is now used in place of ifconfig in documentation recipes (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/pull/600)
  * the intel-mpi-devel-ohpc compatibility package can now be installed independently of the companion compiler
    (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/955)
  * installation recipes have been updated to use chrony instead of ntpd for time synchronization
    (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/1107)
  * packaging for a number of development components has been updated to allow better alternate build flag support. This
    is intended for sites who would like to rebuild from an ohpc provided src.rpm and provide alternate build settings
    (e.g. to apply additional processor-specific optimization flags) (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/1183)
  * slurm configuration example in installation recipes updated to use configless option
    (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/1205)

[Known Issues]

  * This initial RC1 release provides a subset of installation recipes (we expect xCat and PBS Professional for CentOS8
    to return in a future release)
  * Lustre client and BeeGFS are not yet available
  * Several packages with the Intel compiler variant are not available: Boost, Trilinos, and geopm

[Component Additions]

  * libfabric-ohpc                           (1.10.1)
  * ucx-cma-ohpc                             (1.8.0)
  * ucx-ib-ohpc                              (1.8.0)
  * ucx-ohpc                                 (1.8.0)
  * ucx-rdmacm-ohpc                          (1.8.0)

[Component Deprecation]

  * ganglia
  * mpiP
  * ocr
  * mrsh

