----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Version 1.3.5 (13 June 2018)

[Important Highlights/Notices]

  * There are significant changes included in the warewulf-httpd.conf file that ships with the
    warewulf-provision-server-ohpc package. If upgrading from a version prior to OpenHPC v1.3, the updated config file
    will be saved as /etc/httpd/conf.d/warewulf-httpd.conf.rpmnew locally. You will need to copy this new version to the
    production file and restart the web server to ensure correct provisioning behavior. As an example for CentOS:

    [sms]# cp /etc/httpd/conf.d/warewulf-httpd.conf.rpmnew /etc/httpd/conf.d/warewulf-httpd.conf
    [sms]# systemctl restart httpd

[General]

  * updates to support CentOS7.5
  * enabled Lua job submit plugin in SLURM builds (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/697)
  * re-enable jobcomp_elasticsearch plugin in SLURM builds (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/698)
  * fix for stateful provisioning when using Warewulf (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/700)
  * enable X11 build support in SLURM (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/701)
  * rebuild of older compiler/MPI variants using updated dependency schema for dynamic libraries that was introduced
    in OpenHPC v1.3.4 (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/702)
  * fix for stdin redirection issue using OpenMPI with build of newer version, v3.1.0 
    (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/709)
  * updated spack packaging to include missing templates (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/715)
  * fix for PSXE compatibility packages removing ohpc-style modulefiles during package upgrade
    (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/718)
  * updated documentation for NHC configuration (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/741)
  * variety of component version updates and other additions highlighted below

[Component Additions]

  * charliecloud-ohpc                        (0.2.4)

[Component Version Changes]

  * EasyBuild-ohpc                           (3.5.3 -> 3.6.1)
  * R-gnu7-ohpc                              (3.4.4 -> 3.5.0)
