----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Version 1.3.2 (07 September 2017)

[Important Highlights/Notices]

  * There are significant changes included in the warewulf-httpd.conf file that ships with the
    warewulf-provision-server-ohpc package. If upgrading from a version prior to 1.3, the updated config file will be
    saved as /etc/httpd/conf.d/warewulf-httpd.conf.rpmnew locally. You will need to copy this new version to the
    production file and restart the web server to ensure correct provisioning behavior. As an example for CentOS:

    [sms]# cp /etc/httpd/conf.d/warewulf-httpd.conf.rpmnew /etc/httpd/conf.d/warewulf-httpd.conf
    [sms]# systemctl restart httpd

[General]

  * updated backend OBS build system to avoid false package dependences for CentOS (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/451)
  * updated SLURM build to support cgroup plugin (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/476)
  * relocation of several package installs into utils/ subdirectory (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/486)
  * updated PSXE compatibility packages to use pre-install scriptlet to verify locally installed versions instead of
    specific package dependency (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/479)
  * added enablement of dhcpd services to recipes (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/492)
  * adoption of newer 'depends_on' syntax to define Lmod dependencies (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/495)
  * fix to avoid variable replacement for binary sync files in Warewulf (https://github.com/openhpc/ohpc/issues/531)
  * llvm4 compiler variant introduced (providing clang, clang++, and flang compiler frontends)
  * variety of component version updates and other additions highlighted below


[Component Additions]

  * cmake-ohpc                               (3.9.1)
  * llvm4-compilers-ohpc                     (4.0.1)
  * plasma-gnu7-ohpc                         (2.8.0)
  * plasma-intel-ohpc                        (2.8.0)
